==English==
===Etymology===
First attested from [[w:1827|1827]].  [[Back-formation]] from '''[[enthusiasm]]''', from Greek ''entheos'', inspired by a god, from ''en-'', in + ''theos'', god.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːz|-uːz]]

===Transitive verb===
'''to enthuse''' ('''enthusing''', '''enthused''', '''enthused''')

#To cause (someone) to feel enthusiasm.
#:''The novelty of the film enthused the audience.''

